cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the task of removing rain from images using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach to training sub-networks to handle different scales of rain streaks, which involves machine learning and could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic and real images to test the effectiveness of their method, which could fall under categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
